<item>
            <title>[TINKERPOP-1792] Random TraversalSource Selection in GremlinScriptEngine</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TINKERPOP-1792</link>
                <project id="12316520" key="TINKERPOP">TinkerPop</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;GremlinScriptEngine&lt;/tt&gt; implementations make a random &lt;tt&gt;TraversalSource&lt;/tt&gt; selection when processing lambdas. Obviously it should be bound more clearly to the specific &lt;tt&gt;TraversalSource&lt;/tt&gt; the caller requests. Another issue that isn&apos;t completely clear is that bindings passed from the client share the same namespace as &lt;tt&gt;TraversalSource&lt;/tt&gt; bindings which means that if the &lt;tt&gt;TraversalSource&lt;/tt&gt; is &quot;g&quot; then you couldn&apos;t write a traversal like: &lt;tt&gt;withSideEffect(&#8220;g&#8221;, &#8220;hello&#8221;)&lt;/tt&gt;. That could be smarter as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
